### Logger usage
{{- if eq .Logger "slog"}}

```go
// Structured key-value pairs
logger.Info("order fetched", "order_id", id)
logger.Warn("slow query", "duration_ms", elapsed)
logger.Error("fetch failed", "error", err)
```
{{- end}}
{{- if eq .Logger "zap"}}

```go
// Typed fields for zero-allocation logging
logger.Info("order fetched", zap.Int64("order_id", id))
logger.Warn("slow query", zap.Duration("duration", elapsed))
logger.Error("fetch failed", zap.Error(err))
```
{{- end}}
{{- if eq .Logger "zerolog"}}

```go
// Chain builder — always call .Msg() or .Send() at the end
logger.Info().Int64("order_id", id).Msg("order fetched")
logger.Warn().Dur("duration", elapsed).Msg("slow query")
logger.Error().Err(err).Msg("fetch failed")
```
{{- end}}

Import the logger via the interface: `"{{.Module}}/pkg/logger"` — never import the concrete library directly.